arChildNodes.szComment:
Carnage. Broken and battered KNIGHT PENITENT BODIES are lined up on the floor. Donan has positioned them here out of respect. Other Pale Knight bodies are scattered around the area.
The MURAL of DONAN, NAFAIN, and AIRIDAH is in ruins: slashed with claw marks.
When the PLAYER arrives, Donan is dragging a PALE KNIGHT BODY MISSING AN ARM. He places the body next to the line of corpses. 
He crosses the knight’s arm (just one) over the corpse’s own chest, putting the body in a peaceful, dignified position.

Donan approaches another slain pale knight. He’s IMPALED TO A WALL with a CATHEDRAL OF LIGHT STANDARD through his chest.
Donan grips the standard and PULLS. It doesn’t budge at first.
Another YANK and the standard is pulled free. Donan catches the body before it can fall.
Donan drags the corpse over to the line of other bodies.
Donan carefully crosses the arms of the pale knight corpse he just set down. The others have their arms crossed already.
Donan moves his hand over the corpse’s face, a gesture to close the pale knight’s wide, terror-stricken eyes.
Donan rises and walks over to rubble in the room. He looks around, regarding the ruined keep.
Donan sits on a chunk of the rubble to catch his breath. He speaks passionately, trying to justify his previous actions.
Donan wipes the sweat from his face. He stands up.
